Dieser Artikel erläutert den Vorgang der '''Verknüpfung''' eines bestehenden Plattform-Kontos mit einem regulären [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat account|VRChat-Konto]]. 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Platform accounts include pre-existing accounts on the following devices:
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Steam
* Meta
* PICO
* Viveport
* Google
* Discord
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Benefits of a full VRChat account ==
A full VRChat account enables users to:
* Earn [[Special:MyLanguage/Trust Ranks|Trust Ranks]]
* Retain the simplicity of one-click logins
* Apply to enroll in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Creator Economy|Creator Economy]] Program
* Change their screenname
** Removes the generated four-digit '[[wikipedia:Discriminator|discriminator]]' code at the end of their screenname
* Gain access to Login
** {{VRC link|https://vrchat.com/home|VRChat Website}}
** [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat SDK|VRChat SDK]]
* Gain authorization access on platforms with VRChat SSO
** {{VRC link|https://wiki.vrchat.com/|VRChat Wiki}}
** {{VRC link|https://feedback.vrchat.com/|VRChat Feedback Board}}
** [https://ask.vrchat.com/|VRChat VRChat Ask Forums]
** Third-party vendors that utilize VRChat SSO
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Pre-link considerations ==
=== Favorites limit ===
Upon merging, if the total number of favorites from both accounts exceeds the platform's maximum limit, users may retain more favorites than typically allowed. However, to add new favorites, users must remove existing ones to fit within the limit. It is generally advised to link into a fresh account.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Purchase restrictions ===
Users who have made purchases through the [[Special:MyLanguage/Creator Economy|Creator Economy]] on any platform (Steam, Meta, Pico, Viveport, Google) cannot link their accounts into a full VRChat account. This restriction is temporary and expected to be lifted.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Linking process ==
[[File:MainMenuLinkAccountButton.png|alt=A screenshot of the VRChat menu with a visible "Link Account" button.|thumb|Menu with "Link Account" button.]]
To merge a platform account into a full VRChat account, follow these steps:
# Log into the Steam, Meta, Pico, Google, or Viveport account you wish to link.
# Open the Main Menu in VRChat.
# Navigate to '''Settings'''.
# Locate and click the '''Link Account''' button below the Exit option.
#* If the '''Link Account''' button is not visible, you are likely already logged into a full VRChat account.
# Follow the on-screen instructions to link your account.
If there are still difficulties with linking your account, contact VRChat support at {{VRC link|https://vrch.at/support|VRChat Support}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Post-link ==
Linking is permanent and irreversible. Each full VRChat account can be linked to one account from each supported platform simultaneously. It can take up to one day for account data to fully merge. For any issues during or after the process, contact VRChat support at {{VRC link|https://vrch.at/support|VRChat Support}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Linking for Discord accounts ==
[[File:VRC_Discordaccountlink.webp|thumb|A demonstration of a UI element, showing that a user can link their Discord and VRChat account.]] [[File:VRC_loginscreenDiscord.webp|thumb|VRChat's log-in screen, giving the option to log in using Discord.]]
On September 25, 2025<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-25-september-2025 "Developer Update - September 25, 2025"] on ''[https://hello.vrchat.com/blog VRChat's Blog]'' at ''[[hello.vrchat.com]]''. Dated September 25, 2025. Retrieved September 25, 2025.</ref>, a posted [[Developer Update]] demonstrates a future capability to link a VRChat account, and Discord account together. Users will also have the ability to create a platformed [[VRChat account]], and be given the option to log in, using Discord. Additionally, users will be able to unlink their accounts at any time, through Discord or VRChat.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
As of October 16, 2025, the [[Open Beta]] for [https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202541-openbeta 2025.4.1] introduced the ability to log into VRChat, using Discord, as well as linking accounts.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The Discord login feature was officially released in
[https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202541 2025.4.1] , released on November 3.
